records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
This is a really interesting proposition, however, we do not feel that the business in its current form will resonate with our investors.

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition, an existing digital marketing strategy and ideally an engaged community around your brand. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, we just feel you are not ready at this stage. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

What is Studentstay.co.uk?
Studentstay.co.uk is the UK's first student accommodation portal with integrated travel services.

What is Our Vision?
To simplify the process of securing UK student accommodation for the overseas student and provide them with additional products and services throughout their stay in the UK.

Where Are We Right Now?
StudentStay has achieved a room inventory in excess of 30 000 rooms UK-wide since Launch late July 2016, working with the largest Operators in the UK.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
You seem to have a great product with a lot of potential, however, we do not feel that the business in its current form will resonate with our investors.

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition and ideally an existing engaged community. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, but as the model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time if we do not feel you are ready to launch a campaign. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
This is a really interesting proposition, however, we do not feel that the business in its current form will resonate with our investors.

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition, an existing digital marketing strategy and ideally an engaged community around your brand. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, we just feel you are not ready at this stage. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Qualification__c:
We think this is a really interesting concept but, unfortunately, we do not feel that you are at the right stage to continue with the application process. Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition, an existing digital marketing strategy and ideally an engaged community around your brand. You will need to work on the above as well as increasing your traction before considering this method of raising capital.
 
In light of this, we feel that you may benefit from some additional help in preparing to launch. This makes you a potential candidate for the Crowd10 crowdfund readiness programme, which is run by our trusted partner Kirsty Ranger (kirsty@ideasquares.com). Crowd 10 is an initiative that helps startups to get investment ready and go live on Crowdcube - like a Crowdcube Accelerator. We have a strong relationship with Kirsty and she is currently looking for great businesses to work with. We suggest you get in touch with her as a Crowdcube referral so that she can talk to you in more detail about what the programme offers.
 
We have also partnered with G by Grant Thornton (read more about our partnership here https://www.crowdcube.com/explore/2017/04/14/getting-crowdcube-ready-with-g-by-grant-thornton) to help startups get investment ready and we have negotiated a reduced price for startups that are going to launch on the Crowdcube platform. This service is more extensive but also more expensive than the Crowd10 programme and so at your stage of growth I feel that working with Kirsty would be more suitable.
 
Alternatively, our following partners may be of use in your search for investment:
 
- Funding Options (www.crowdcube.com/pg/alternative-funding-options-1746) is a platform that lets you compare quotes for your business from a number of different finance providers
- Crowdfunder.co.uk is a crowdfunding platform that works with various projects, businesses & non-profits
- StartupLoans.co.uk offers a government-backed financing and mentoring solutions for entrepreneurs looking to start a business.

You are welcome to resubmit a new or revised application at any time.

records.Achievements__c:
The Players Republic is a brand new sporting agency founded by two of UK sport's most influential people - best-selling author Jon Smith and top cricket agent Adam Wheatley.

Both have worked extensively with some of the biggest names in the business and have left a lasting impression on British sport. Jon was tasked with introducing American favourites NBA, NFL and others to these shores and managed the entire England football team, during which he developing the Team England vehicle that the FA still uses to this day.

Their new mission is to find the best up-and-coming talent, secure their image rights, nurture them and eventually negotiate with a major club to get them a professional contract. They want to spot the players of tomorrow and give them their chance today.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
This is a really interesting proposition, however, we do not feel that the business in its current form will resonate with our investors.

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition, an existing digital marketing strategy and ideally an engaged community around your brand. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

We also do not currently work with property development or management companies as it is not suited to the business model we operate.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, we just feel you are not ready at this stage. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
We feel that your business will fail to resonate with investors on our platform due to lack of scalability. Crowdcube, as a platform, aims to attract high-growth-potential companies who have the ability to provide a return to investors with credible exit strategies. Our investors expect to receive a return in the event that the company they have invested in makes an 'exit' in the future and because of your business model we feel that you will not be able to achieve the kind of exit that our investors are looking for. 

Our decision to not progress your application at this time is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business. The funding model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time and ours going down this road, pulling everything together to ultimately not fund. It is a subjective decision made on the basis that, at its current stage, we would not be confident that your business will attract sufficient investment to reach its funding target.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
We feel that your business will fail to resonate with investors on our platform due to lack of scalability. Crowdcube, as a platform, aims to attract high-growth-potential companies who have the ability to provide a return to investors with credible exit strategies. Our investors expect to receive a return in the event that the company they have invested in makes an 'exit' in the future and because of your business model we feel that you will not be able to achieve the kind of exit that our investors are looking for. Different types of exits include a trade sale, IPO or share buyback, not dividend payments or revenue share.

Our decision to not progress your application at this time is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business. The funding model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time and ours going down this road, pulling everything together to ultimately not fund. It is a subjective decision made on the basis that, at its current stage, we would not be confident that your business will attract sufficient investment to reach its funding target.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
We feel that your business will fail to resonate with investors on our platform due to lack of scalability. Crowdcube, as a platform, aims to attract high-growth-potential companies who have the ability to provide a return to investors with credible exit strategies. Our investors expect to receive a return in the event that the company they have invested in makes an 'exit' in the future and because of your business model we feel that you will not be able to achieve the kind of exit that our investors are looking for. Different types of exits include a trade sale, IPO or share buyback, not dividend payments or revenue share.

Our decision to not progress your application at this time is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business. The funding model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time and ours going down this road, pulling everything together to ultimately not fund. It is a subjective decision made on the basis that, at its current stage, we would not be confident that your business will attract sufficient investment to reach its funding target.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
We feel that your business will fail to resonate with investors on our platform due to lack of scalability. Crowdcube, as a platform, aims to attract high-growth-potential companies who have the ability to provide a return to investors with credible exit strategies. Our investors expect to receive a return in the event that the company they have invested in makes an 'exit' in the future and because of your business model as well as point 7 in your Crowdcube pitch document, we feel that you will not be able to achieve the kind of exit that our investors are looking for in the right time frame. Different types of exits include a trade sale, IPO or share buyback, not dividend payments or revenue share.

Our decision to not progress your application at this time is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business. The funding model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time and ours going down this road, pulling everything together to ultimately not fund. It is a subjective decision made on the basis that, at its current stage, we would not be confident that your business will attract sufficient investment to reach its funding target.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Qualification__c:
Firstly, we really enjoyed looking through your product line and technology and there seems to be an exciting market opportunity. However, whilst your company has extremely exciting prospects, we feel that the business in its current form is unlikely to resonate well with investors on our platform. From past experience, without a significant amount of cornerstone investment you would struggle to fund successfully at this stage. 

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition, a strong brand and ideally an engaged community around your product. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website, develop your brand image and establish a social media presence before considering this method of raising capital. It would be useful to look at some existing pitches on the site and request their “business plans”; these are typically in pitch deck Powerpoint format and will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, we just feel you are not ready at this stage. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Qualification__c:
We think this is a really interesting concept but, unfortunately, we do not feel that you are at the right stage to continue with the application process. Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition, an existing digital marketing strategy and ideally an engaged community around your brand. You will need to work on the above as well as increasing your traction before considering this method of raising capital.
 
In light of this, we feel that you may benefit from some additional help in preparing to launch. This makes you a potential candidate for the Crowd10 crowdfund readiness programme, which is run by our trusted partner Kirsty Ranger (kirsty@ideasquares.com). Crowd 10 is an initiative that helps startups to get investment ready and go live on Crowdcube - like a Crowdcube Accelerator. We have a strong relationship with Kirsty and she is currently looking for great businesses to work with. We suggest you get in touch with her as a Crowdcube referral so that she can talk to you in more detail about what the programme offers.
 
We have also partnered with G by Grant Thornton (read more about our partnership here https://www.crowdcube.com/explore/2017/04/14/getting-crowdcube-ready-with-g-by-grant-thornton) to help startups get investment ready and we have negotiated a reduced price for startups that are going to launch on the Crowdcube platform. This service is more extensive but also more expensive than the Crowd10 programme and so at your stage of growth I feel that working with Kirsty would be more suitable.
 
Alternatively, our following partners may be of use in your search for investment:
 
- Funding Options (www.crowdcube.com/pg/alternative-funding-options-1746) is a platform that lets you compare quotes for your business from a number of different finance providers
- Crowdfunder.co.uk is a crowdfunding platform that works with various projects, businesses & non-profits
- StartupLoans.co.uk offers a government-backed financing and mentoring solutions for entrepreneurs looking to start a business.

You are welcome to resubmit a new or revised application at any time.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition and ideally an existing engaged community. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

We find that concept-stage companies fail to resonate with investors on our platform unless they have proof of concept that verifies their underlying assumptions, initial traction and/or seasoned entrepreneurs with previous exit experience. 

You are welcome to resubmit a new or revised application at any time.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
This looks like a fantastic opportunity, however, we feel that your business will fail to resonate with investors on our platform due to lack of scalability. Crowdcube, as a platform, aims to attract high-growth-potential companies who have the ability to provide a return to investors with credible exit strategies. Our investors expect to receive a return in the event that the company they have invested in makes an 'exit' in the future and because of your business model we feel that you will not be able to achieve the kind of exit that our investors are looking for. Different types of exits include a trade sale, IPO or share buyback, not dividend payments or revenue share.

Our decision to not progress your application at this time is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business. The funding model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time and ours going down this road, pulling everything together to ultimately not fund. It is a subjective decision made on the basis that, at its current stage, we would not be confident that your business will attract sufficient investment to reach its funding target.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
This is an amazing concept and we feel that there is a huge need for what you are working to create, however, we do not feel that the business in its current form will resonate with our investors.

We find that concept-stage companies fail to resonate with investors on our platform unless they have proof of concept that verifies their underlying assumptions, initial traction and/or seasoned entrepreneurs with previous exit experience. 

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition and ideally an existing engaged community. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, but as the model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time if we do not feel you are ready to launch a campaign. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c:
You have an interesting concept with a lot of potential, however, we do not feel that the business in its current form will resonate with our investors.

Crowdfunding is a very public and brand-oriented form of raising finance that relies heavily on having a clear value proposition and ideally an existing engaged community. You will need to work on the visual aspects of your website and pitch deck before considering this method of raising capital. I would also recommend that you look at some existing pitches on the site and request their business plans; this will give you some ideas on creating a more visually compelling business plan to present to investors. For our guidelines on this, please refer to https://files-crowdcube-com.s3.amazonaws.com/portal_id_1/Crowdcube-Business-Plan-Standards.pdf.

Our decision not to progress your application is by no means a reflection of the concept or ultimate success of the business, but as the model we operate is all or nothing, we don't want to waste your time if we do not feel you are ready to launch a campaign. We encourage you to come back to us when you have worked on the above.

records.Achievements__c:
Think of the Netflix for the Recruitment industry, Blecret plans to change the recruitment industry forever.
Blecret will stop the current norm of companies paying thousands of pounds to recruitment agencies, each and every time they find them a successful candidate for one of their latest job openings, by offering a flat-fee, subscription based recruitment service.
The flat-fee will dramatically reduce expenditure of recruitment for the client, whilst allowing for continual cash-flow.

records.Reason_for_disapproval_Reg_Interest__c: We feel that your business will fail to resonate with investors on our platform due to lack of scalability. Crowdcube, as a platform, aims to attract high-growth-potential companies who have the ability to provide a return to investors with credible exit strategies. Our investors expect to receive a return in the event that the company they have invested in makes an 'exit' in the future and because of your business model we feel that you will not be able to achieve the kind of exit that our investors are looking for. Different types of exits include a trade sale, IPO or share buyback, not dividend payments or revenue share.
